 "floorPolicy": {
  "description": "HIL D2 floor policy (docs/dev/mirror-flicker-2026-07-12.md, refinement 2): a REBASE BETWEEN PREDICTIONS emits NO baseline dip \u2014 the floor tick applies the CACHED latest prediction against the NEW linearization. A cold brick (no prediction yet) still emits the raw baseline (planner decision 4), and an unhealthy rebase (feedForward=false) floors raw. Steps run in order on one brick; `expected` is the emission for that step. Pinned on BOTH implementations: the native ComposeStream (core/test/45) drives the real brick; the TS suite (app/test/compose-node.test.ts) recomputes each expected from the composeVolts algebra.",
  "tolerance": 1e-09,
  "steps": [
   {
    "op": "rebase",
    "note": "cold floor: no prediction cached yet -> RAW vPid",
    "rebase": {
     "vPid": {
